"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/1NKVRv4vr8VlSuGNFaHMA.png?height=278&width=1314)\\n\\n## Whatâ€™s it all about?\\n\\nScrums are online workshops for [Collaborators](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/onyNgQAi-2VKGNTDGYK9vf20AK-k7i-3qot58G4Qo54) to quickly discuss tactics, get support and build consensus for best action. \\n\\n## Ground Rules\\n\\n* Use a laptop in a quiet environment (not cell phone)\\n* Start the call with your mic on **mute**. Feel free to type into the chat.\\n* Raise a ðŸ‘‹ if you want to open your mic\\n* Only switch on your mic when indicated by the **Speaker**\\n* Itâ€™s rude to be late, but itâ€™s okay to leave early\\n\\n## Speaker and Scribe\\n\\nFor big groups, the Lead can delegate tasks to a **Speaker** and a **Scribe**. The Lead should still announce the scrums and be present in the call.\\n\\nðŸ–‹ **Scribe**\\n\\n* Draft the agenda\\n* Choose a date and time\\n* Take Notes during the meeting\\n\\nðŸ—£ **Speaker**\\n\\n* Mediate between members\\n* Assign break-away rooms\\n* Ensure everyone gets fair air time\\n\\n## ðŸ”¸ðŸ”¸ Example Agenda ðŸ”¸ðŸ”¸\\n\\n### Welcome\\n\\n1. Speaker welcomes members. Make some social time for personal greetings between all members.\\n2. News Announcements: Incoming/outgoing team members, new features, events and accomplishments.\\n3. Reminder of Ground Rules if necessary (ex. new members)\\n\\n### Pending points of previous meeting\\n\\nAt the end of the last Scrum, notes were posted into the Room with the heading **\\\"Scrum Notes - \\\\[DATE\\\\]\\\"** Read these out and discuss if pending or resolved with corresponding members.\\n\\n### Today (New)\\n\\n* Agenda. Direction, Momentum and order of topics.\\n* **The Round Table:** Members give 3-minute questions (or statements), prompting responses from other members who can raise a hand and have 5 minutes to phrase their opinion.\\n* **In Summary**: Final thoughts from experienced Managers. Action Plan (scribe!). What's working/not working. Scrum format? Suggestions from the tea m.\\n\\n### Close Scrum\\n\\n* Make **Action Plan**\\n* **Scribe** takes a \\\"screenshot selfie\\\" of the meeting\\n* Goodbyes - *Appreciation to the **Speaker** and **Scribe** please!*\\n* Post the Scrum Notes in the Incubator, with the photo and giving credit to the Speaker and Scribe for their efforts.\",\"timestamp\":1639134067,\"title\":\"Scrums\"},\"digest\":\"63i6GPIBoYjId039yeEXMwNFTWVVL0Mjjj6WPrrJhDE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"34suyCfnLUoFM02SOhmJJJ9iXgiiL5kC6iPH6Fv3LXk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"jtVAiplEVAd0RPMj7L2P0umm9wTPdvk-kh1vAJTvwJc\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"P48Sc2sqtZ8ZJrsPKGNuk6x-l71k8slOCCIDgbTpsLKsVjm9v3rGUF8E9NNcBsWiiqY0Q2KZRYIY91S3VnZlew\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x57d0f7cbea22222afabed23e09ac819f759269ea4cca2a83cdd992ddf3ffe88d22a7afd325b70c3c1ae7dee6f5fc8e22188ba69c589cf1f0528e258261121ae51b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"34suyCfnLUoFM02SOhmJJJ9iXgiiL5kC6iPH6Fv3LXk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"jtVAiplEVAd0RPMj7L2P0umm9wTPdvk-kh1vAJTvwJc\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"63i6GPIBoYjId039yeEXMwNFTWVVL0Mjjj6WPrrJhDE\"}"